 A. copa infusion is used in traditional medicine for the treatment of colds, pneumonia, hypertension, pain, for gall bladder problems, as digestive, often combined with sodium bicarbonate. The infusion mixed with milk is used for stomach pain, cold, and colic. In the form of baths or incense, it serves to combat “mal de aire” and toothache. As a bath, it serves for bone pain. People attribute sedative properties to the species the ability to cause vivid dreams (
 Giberti, 1983; 
 Montes and Wilkomirsky, 1985; 
 De Nucci, 1988; 
 Paniagua-Zambrana et al., 2020).
